Quite the contrary. Javascript has a strange, ugly hybrid of lexical and function scope that is not that of Scheme, which I suspect that Bob understands very well given his interest in languages (and that he works on a language that compiles to JS).<p>This is not lexical scoping:<p><pre><code>    function example(k) {
        function ugly() {return i};
        for (var i = 0; i < k; i++) {}
        return ugly;
    }
    example(4)() // => 4</code></pre>

